docblock.long-description:
Responsible for taking a class based oject and calling it's setters with matching params from a standard object.
The purpose of the hydrator is setting properties of models with setters. Model setters should only contain one parameter.
Model setters can accept a scaler or type hinted class. Values for setters without type hints are passed as compound types or scalers.

docblock.description: Hydrating a class object from a hashed array uses an **Adder**. addSomething().
Hydrating a class object from standard object calls a **Setter** for each of it's properties.

docblock.long-description:
Takes an object and tries to hydrate it with another.
Uses methods prefixed with "set" to set values.
If the payload is an array (hash) it will call a method prefixed with "add". This is required in order to find the type hint.

Checks the method signature for a type hint, if one is found hydrate is called and the result is sent to the method.
If there is no type hint in the method signature the value is used without attempting hydration.
